ME: What is NLP?
AI: NLP stands for Natural Language Processing â€” a field of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that focuses on enabling computers to understand, interpret, and generate human language.

Hereâ€™s a clear breakdown ğŸ‘‡

ğŸ§  Definition

Natural Language Processing (NLP) is a combination of linguistics, computer science, and machine learning techniques that allow computers to read, understand, and respond to text or speech in a human-like way.

ğŸ§© Main Components of NLP
Component	Description	Example
Tokenization	Splitting text into words or sentences	â€œI love NLPâ€ â†’ [â€œIâ€, â€œloveâ€, â€œNLPâ€]
Part-of-Speech Tagging	Identifying grammar roles (noun, verb, adjective)	â€œloveâ€ â†’ verb
Named Entity Recognition (NER)	Detecting names, places, dates	â€œElon Musk founded SpaceX.â€ â†’ â€œElon Muskâ€ = Person
Sentiment Analysis	Detecting emotions or opinions in text	â€œThis product is amazing!â€ â†’ Positive
Language Modeling	Predicting next words or generating text	ChatGPT completing your sentence
Machine Translation	Translating between languages	English â†’ Bangla
Speech Recognition	Converting spoken words to text	Voice typing on your phone
Text Summarization	Creating concise summaries	Turning a long article into bullet points
âš™ï¸ How NLP Works

Data Collection â€“ Gather human language data (text, audio, etc.)

Preprocessing â€“ Clean and prepare data (remove punctuation, stopwords, etc.)

Feature Extraction â€“ Represent words using numbers (word embeddings like Word2Vec, BERT, etc.)

Model Training â€“ Train machine learning models to perform tasks (classification, translation, etc.)

Evaluation â€“ Measure performance using metrics like accuracy, precision, recall.

ğŸ’¡ Real-World Applications

Chatbots (like ChatGPT, Siri, Alexa)

Google Translate

Spam email filtering

